article.headline: Penn 34, Cornell 0
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Keiffer Garton threw two touchdown passes and ran for a score to lead Penn to a 34-0 rout of Cornell on Saturday. Garton scored on an 8-yard run in the second quarter as the Ivy League champion Quakers (8-2, 7-0) built a 20-0 halftime lead. Garton went 5-for-7 for 81 yards passing, including touchdown passes of 9 yards to Luke Nawrocki and 25 yards to Kyle Derham in the third quarter. The Quakers close out the season with eight straight wins, while the Big Red (2-8, 1-6) have lost eight in a row. The Quakers held Cornell to four first downs and 110 yards total offense. The Big Red managed only 30 yards rushing on 28 carries. Ben Ganter generated most of the offense for the Big Red, going 7-for-18 passing for 69 yards and an interception.
